<HEADLINE> 24 Killed, 25 Injured in Accident in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-four people were killed and
25 others injured on Tuesday in a road accident involving a bus, a
taxi and a truck in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place at a highway junction near Suez, a town
140 kilometers east of Cairo, the country's Middle East News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
A truck from the Red Sea town of Zafarana collided with a bus
carrying workers of the Suez Cement Company on their way to work
for the early day shift, security sources said.
</P>
<P>
The bus driver lost control of the vehicle, which ran into a
parking car, the sources said. They attributed the accident to
high speed and reckless driving at the crossroads.
</P>
<P>
Most of the victims were the workers of the cement company. The
drivers of the truck and the bus were also killed. The injured
have been taken to hospitals in Suez.
</P>
<P>
Road accidents are common in Egypt due to high speed and poor
road conditions. According to Interior Ministry reports, an
average of 6,000 people are killed in traffic accidents in Egypt
each year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
