<HEADLINE> Lebanese Intellectuals Support Accused Singer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon's intellectuals on
Tuesday held a mass rally to declare solidarity with the
country's leading singer and composer Marcel Khalife accused of
allegedly insulting Islam.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of journalists, writers and politicians participated
in the rally, which was held at the headquarters of the
country's Press Association in Beirut, and signed a petition.
</P>
<P>
They said in the petition that the signatories assumed
responsibility for helping Khalife produce an album for which
he was facing blasphemy charges for including a Koranic verse
in one of his songs.
