<HEADLINE> Four British Tourists Killed in Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Four British tourists were
killed Tuesday in a road accident near Cyprus' southern Larnaca
town, Cyprus News Agency (CNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The fatalities occurred when the car hired by the tourists had
a head-on collision with another two cars.
</P>
<P>
The victims were two couples, but their names were not
disclosed.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened on the main highway leading to the
eastern holiday resort of Ayia Napa when the victims' car entered
the opposite side of the road.
</P>
<P>
In Cyprus, driving should be conducted on the left side of the
road, as in Britain. Investigations into the accident are
underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
