<HEADLINE> 560 Ethiopians to Benefit From Surgical Camps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Some 560 impaired Ethiopians
will benefit from the surgical camps sponsored by the Rotary
International, which kicked off in Addis Ababa Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement by the Rotary International, a
27-member international rotarian corps will perform operations for
treating and rehabilitating over 120 polio-crippled children, 400
visually impaired persons and about 40 patients requiring plastic
surgery.
</P>
<P>
The 10-day surgical camps will help improve the surviving
chances of polio-affected children and reduce the burden on their
families and the community, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The surgical camps project is being financed by the Rotary
International, Rotary Clubs and rotarians in Addis Ababa, the
Ethiopian News Agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
