<HEADLINE> Coach Accident Kills 12 Guatemalans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Twelve died and over 30 were
injured, six gravely, in a bus accident in Quiche province in
northern Guatemala, official sources said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Guatemala City, the accident occurred
Monday evening when the bus, belonging to the Linda Orquida
company, fell down a ravine.
</P>
<P>
The injured were taken to the National Hospital of Santa Cruz.
</P>
<P>
The initial investigation suggested that the accident occurred
due to steering failure. 
</P>
