<HEADLINE> S. African Agricultural Union to Restructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The South African
Agricultural Union is set to restructure in a bid to strengthen
its partnership with the new Land and Agriculture Minister Thoko
Didiza.
</P>
<P>
At the organization's annual congress, which started Tuesday,
delegates were considering commercially-driven land reforms to
boost rural development and land reform following several meetings
between the new minister and the union.
</P>
<P>
Executive director of the agricultural union, Jack Raath said
the issue of rural development and boosting emerging farmers would
also be a key issue at the conference.
</P>
<P>
"The message from the new minister is that government is
looking for new partners in farming. It is a positive message,"
Raath said.
</P>
<P>
The congress focus on a proposed name change for the union to
that of Agri-SA. Raath said if the congress agreed to this, it
would be the last congress under the banner of the South African
Agricultural Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
