<HEADLINE> Schroeder: Athens Visit Confirms Successful Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 5 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Gerhard
Schroeder said here Tuesday that his visit to Athens had confirmed
the successful cooperation between Greece and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder, who is in Athens on a two-day working visit, added
that his visit further strengthened the already good relations
between the two countries in all sectors.
</P>
<P>
The visit had also had a positive effect on the two countries'
joint obligations to the European Union (EU) and the Balkan
region, he said.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder noted that Germany wanted to bring together the two
countries and also wanted to take advantage of Greek experiences
in the region.
</P>
<P>
As for Turkey's accession to the EU, he said that Turkey had
taken one step closer to the EU after his talks with Greek Prime
Minister Costas Simitis.
</P>
<P>
During their talks Monday, both sides agreed to search for ways
to make possible an endorsement of Turkey's candidacy for EU
membership by the Helsinki EU summit in December. 
</P>
</TEXT>
