<HEADLINE> 82 Tons of Drugs Seized in Iran in 5 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Over 82 tons of narcotic drugs
were seized in Iran in the first five months of the current
Iranian year which started from March 21, the Islamic Republic
News Agency (IRNA) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ali Shafiel, director general of the law enforcement forces
(LEF) in charge of anti-drug campaign, told IRNA that the drugs
included 1,773 kilograms of heroin, 3,113 kilograms of morphine,
69,000 kilograms of opium, 80,061 kilograms of hashish and 117
kilograms of other kinds of drugs.
</P>
<P>
The amount was 22,000 kilograms more than that of the
corresponding period last Iranian year, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,669 members of the LEF were killed in anti-drug
campaigns last year and 25 LEF members have been killed so far
this year, Shafiel said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
