<HEADLINE> Mexican MPs Call for Immediate Lifting of Embargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, October 5 (Xinhua) -- A visiting Mexican
parliamentary delegation on Tuesday called for immediate lifting
of the nine-year-old United Nations sanctions on Iraq, the Iraqi
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to the Iraqi News Agency, the Mexican delegation
also said its visit to Iraq is an important step on the track to
activate the relations between Mexico and Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The delegation said the Mexican parliament will arrange a
celebration next June with the participation of parliamentarians
from different countries in which the issue of the embargo on
Iraq will be the main subject to be discussed.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. imposed sweeping economic sanctions on Iraq following
its 1990 invasion of Kuwait. 
