<HEADLINE> Current Account Deficit Reduces in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Greece's current account deficit
reduced by 40.3 percent to 1.425 billion euros in January-April of
this year from 2.5 billion euros in the same period of last year,
the Bank of Greece announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released Tuesday, the central bank attributed
the drop in the current account deficit mainly to an improvement
in the trade deficit, which reduced to 4.807 billion euros from
5.535 billion euros in the same four-month period of last year.
</P>
<P>
In April, the current account deficit fell to 396 million euros
from 868 million euros in the same month of 1998 while the trade
deficit stood at 1.242 billion euros from 1.504 billion euros in
the same month of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
