<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali Food Products Not Properly Labeled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Food products made in Nepal do
not have labels to provide information to the consumers, the
official RSS news agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
RSS said this was disclosed at an interaction program organized
by the Integrated Biologists Research Group here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According the group, labels used in food products should give
the name of the product, raw materials used, date of production
and batch number, date of expiry, weight, name and address of the
producer, trademark, price, specialty of production, color and
preservatives used, method for storing and warning.
</P>
<P>
But most food products in Nepal do not have or only have part
of the contents mentioned above, according to a research.
</P>
<P>
Pediatrician Sitaram Shrestha said baby food products should
give detailed information about the raw materials used, method of
feeding and production and expiry dates, but the baby food
produced in Nepal does not meet these requirements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
