<DOCNO> XIE19991006.0051 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PIA Publishes Persistency Figures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The Personal Investment Authority
(PIA) Tuesday published the results of its fifth annual survey of
persistency (lapse) rates of life and pensions policies.
</P>
<P>
The PIA resolves to maintain its tough approach to firms with
poor results. The firms with poor persistency records would be
asked to provide an explanation.
</P>
<P>
The survey shows that overall rates of persistency continue to
be low, with no improvement at all for regular premium policies,
25 percent of which lapse within three years and 30 percent lapse
within four years.
</P>
<P>
Joe Palmer, chairman of the PIA, said, "The PIA Board remains
very disappointed with firms with consistently poor persistency
where the underlying factors involve rule breaches and
mis-selling."
</P>
<P>
"The follow-up action we have undertaken on previous reports
shows firms that they cannot be complacent," he warned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
