<HEADLINE> Pak to Enhance Strategic Ties With China: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Foreign Minister
Sartaj Aziz Tuesday reiterated Pakistan's commitment to expand and
enhance its strategic partnership with China for peace and
development in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking at a dinner hosted here, which was attended by
Pakistan Senate Chairman Wasim Sajjad and other six cabinet
members, to mark the Golden Jubilee of the founding of the
People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said the most important feature of
Pak-China relationship is the commonality of "our perceptions and
views on all contemporary issues."
</P>
<P>
"Our overall understanding is rooted in our vision of the
future world: a just, fair and coercion-free world as dreamt by
the eminent founding fathers of China and Pakistan."
</P>
<P>
Aziz said the Pak-China relations have been fostered and
nurtured with great care by the two governments and peoples and
stand as a shining example of a model friendship based on the Five
Principles of Peaceful Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
