other in difficult times. In fact, we are friends in weal and woe.
For us in Pakistan this time-tested and all-weather relationship
is a great source of strength and confidence."
</P>
<P>
Aziz lauded the exceptional achievements of the Chinese people,
saying the half-a-century that has passed since the People's
Republic was founded has been replete with astounding successes
for China.
</P>
<P>
This year is no exception, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Macao will return to the motherland in December just as Hong
Kong did in 1997, and just like Taiwan will, one day," he added.
</P>
<P>
Aziz said China's constant opposition to regional and global
hegemonism and its role in promoting a multipolar, just and
equitable world economic and political order has won her universal
respect and admiration.
</P>
<P>
China's policies, he said, have a special significance for the
developing world.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the confidence that China will continue to
strengthen its cooperation with the developing countries to
promote their legitimate rights and interests. 
