<HEADLINE> EDS-Update with more information South Korea Reports Accident of Nuclear Leakage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Twenty two people were exposed to
radiation after a heavy-water leakage at around 7 p.m. local time
Monday at the Wolsang Nuclear plant in North Kyongsan province of
South Korea, the South Korean Science and Technology Ministry said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said all the 45 liters of heavy water leaked out
has been retrieved and no environment could be polluted as the
leakage failed to run out of the plant.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at the No. 3 unit of the plant which
suspended operation for maintenance on September 23 when the 22
engineers of the South Korean Power Corporation were engaging in
the maintenance job of a cooling water pump.
</P>
<P>
The corporation said the 22 workers were exposed to radiation
measured at between 0.006 mSv and 4.5 mSv.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said a team of nuclear specialists will go to the
plant to investigate cause of the accident. 
</P>
