headquarters and did not verify the authenticity of information
from its sources.
</P>
<P>
"The SADC Allied Forces would like to inform both the regional
and international community that we have always issued communiques
but nobody seems to have bothered to investigate the numerous
cease-fire violations which have been perpetrated by the rebels
and their allies," he said.
</P>
<P>
Cease-fire violations over the past week were at Momongo, Sambo
and Kileta villages, said the commander of the allied forces
fighting for DRC President Laurent Kabila. 
