<HEADLINE> Uganda's Central Bank to Pay Depositors of Closed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Uganda, the
country's central bank, has finalized preparations to pay the
outstanding unpaid private depositors of the International Credit
Bank which was closed last year.
</P>
<P>
Payments to the bona fide private depositors excluding
government departments, parastatals and related accounts will
commence on October 11, the central bank said in a press release
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It called upon all private depositors of the closed commercial
bank to cooperate with the officials to ensure the success of this
exercise.
</P>
<P>
The International Credit Bank was closed by the central bank
for huge inside-lending and mismanagement.
</P>
<P>
In the biggest financial sector reform in its history, the
central bank closed three commercial banks last year and two more
this year, sending shock waves among the average depositors and
the ruling elite. 
</P>
