<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Reserves Increase in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The foreign currency and gold
reserves of Romania's National Bank (BNR) reached over 2.46
billion U.S. dollars at the end of September, going up by 356
million dollars against the beginning of the month, according to a
BNR statement released on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In September, the foreign currency reserve was of 1.47 billion
U.S. dollars, 199 million more than in August. BNR continued the
payments for the foreign debt service, repaying 40.4 million U.S.
dollars in the month. The bank's reserves increased however,
because of foreign currency purchase on the domestic market, worth
203 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold stock remained a total 101.6 tons over the same
period, but its value increased by 157 million dollars, due to
price fluctuations on the international market.
</P>
<P>
With more than USD 2 billion of the foreign debt paid in the
first half of 1999, the BNR's main objective is to increase its
reserves. So, it consolidates its position of net buyer of hard
currency on the domestic interbank market. The reserve will also
increase with sums resulted from international loan agreements,
said the BNR officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
