<HEADLINE> Countdown on for Netaid Concerts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Final preparations are
under way for the three NetAid concerts on October 9 which will
raise much needed support for poverty and humanitarian programs
in developing countries, a release from the United Nations
Development Program said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The concerts are set to take place at Wembley Stadium in
London, at the Palais des Nations in Geneva and in Giants
Stadium in New Jersey, the United States.
</P>
<P>
NetAid is a long-term initiative created by the United Nations
Development Program and Cisco Systems to help end extreme
poverty. It combines the power of the internet, the global reach
of television and radio and the commitment of world-renowned
artists and producers to inspire action against poverty.
</P>
<P>
The concerts will be one of the most widely broadcast
programs for social change in history, and will also be
webcast. The initiative includes the launch of one of the
world's most powerful websites, www.netaid.org.
</P>
<P>
The website will create opportunities for people to learn,
contribute time and money, exchange ideas and join with those
leading the fight against extreme poverty.  
</P>
