<HEADLINE> HKFE Appoints Two New Independent Directors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Futures Exchange
(HKFE) announced Wednesday that Alfred Fung Kwok Chor and Robert
Sze Tsai To have been appointed to its board as independent
directors.
</P>
<P>
The appointments increase the number of independent directors
from four to six out of a total of 15 directors.
</P>
<P>
"The addition of independent directors reflects the exchange's
commitment to openness and transparency," Chairman Geoffrey Yeh
said.
</P>
<P>
Fung, a Hong Kong native, studied law in London. His experience
includes work in North America as a consultant to law firms in the
United States and Canada. He is now a barrister-at-law and head of
his chambers in Hong Kong. Fung is a member of the Hong Kong Bar,
the UK Bar, the British Columbia Bar and Law Society, and the
Singapore Law Society.
</P>
<P>
Sze was born in Shanghai. He joined Price Waterhouse London in
1967 as a chartered accountant and was transferred to Hong Kong in
1971. He became a partner in 1974 and remained with the firm until
he reached its mandatory retirement age in 1996. Sze now serves as
a non-executive director of several listed companies in Hong Kong
including Asia Satellite Telecommunications Holdings and Dah Sing
Financial Holdings (the holding company of Dah Sing Bank).
</P>
<P>
The HKFE is a leading futures and options marketplace in the
Asia Pacific region, with a membership of more than 130 companies,
including a number of major international institutions. The
exchange is actively diversifying its product base, which now
includes currency, interest rate and equity-based products.
</P>
</TEXT>
