<HEADLINE> HK to Hold Asia's Largest Internet Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Internet World Asia @ Hong
Kong'99 will present Asia's largest Internet conference and
exhibition at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center from
November 3 to 5, organizers announced here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
As part of the Internet World Asia @ Hong Kong'99, the
conference assembles the premier, cutting-edge leaders of the
Internet industry from around the world to deliver thought-
provoking discussions and analysis on all aspects of the on-line
world. The luminaries will detail the best strategies from North
America, Asia and Europe to help companies succeed in using the
latest Internet technologies and business strategies.
</P>
<P>
Internet World Asia @ Hong Kong'99 keynotes feature top
Internet executives, including Alan Meckler, JoAnn Patrick-Ezzell,
GM O'Connell and others.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the three-day conference program features six in-
depth industry-specific vertical tracks covering more than 60
sessions. Businesses can discover the latest developments at Web
Development Forum, preview cool new Internet devices and
applications during the Enterprise Internet Technology Symposium,
learn the secrets to measurable advertising results in the Asian
Internet Advertising Forum, or network with other business leaders
in the Asian E-Business Summit and Internet Financial Services
Forum.
</P>
<P>
Start-up companies and venture capitalists alike will be
interested in the special Internet Investment Forum. In addition,
new Launch-Pad East features the hottest Asian start-ups, each
less than 18 months out of the gate. More than 50 luminaries will
meet in the conference, exchanging views and experiences in the
interactive presentations and discussion sessions.
</P>
<P>
In face of the changing market environment, Internet
applications play a crucial role in business advancement, implying
that those who are able to keep in line with the digital economy
are winning the battle in advance. This world-class conference
delivers discussion and answers on essential issues regarding
Internet application and its impact and role in enhancing
specified industry business.
</P>
<P>
"This will be the largest conference we have held in Asia -- a
testament to the growing importance of the Internet across all
industries in the region," noted Michael Westcott, Penton Media's
managing director in the Asia Pacific region. "It is the only
conference in Hong Kong which strives to bring IT, business, and
investment all under one roof," he said. 
</P>
