<HEADLINE> Chinese Cagers Beat Asian All-Star Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese men's basketball
team again showed their dominance in the continent when they
easily beat an Asian All-Star squad 108-73 in the 1999 All-Star
Extravaganza here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, which were crowned as the Asian champions
with a unbeaten record in Fukuka of Japan a month ago, changed
their line-ups every 10 minutes and led all the way to take the
exhibition by 35 points.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team led the first half 47-29.
</P>
<P>
But the Asian All-Star squad shined during the halftime when
South Korean sharpshooter Hur Jae outshot China's Sun Jun to win
the 3-point competition and Yasseen Mahmoud of Qatar soared high
to capture the slam dunk title.
</P>
<P>
The Asian All-star team includes players from seven countries
and regions of Japan, South Korea, the Philippines, Qatar, Syria,
Chinese Taipei and Hong Kong of China. 
