<HEADLINE> HK to Build 3.36 Billion U.S. Dollars Sewage Disposal Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is planning to build
a strategic sewage disposal project with a total investment of 3.
36 billion U.S. dollars, Hong Kong Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The project, named the Strategic Sewage Disposal Scheme, is
being implemented as quickly as possible, Tung said in his annual
policy address.
</P>
<P>
The first stage of the scheme alone will cost a total of 1.06
billion U.S. dollars and the total cost for the remaining works
will reach an estimated 2.3 billion U.S. dollars, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
As part of the first stage of the scheme, "we are building a
massive network of tunnels 150 meters below the surface of the
Kowloon peninsula," the chief executive said.
</P>
<P>
The scheme also includes a sewage treatment works on
Stonecutters Island and a submarine pipeline to carry treated
sewage to the western seabed of the Victoria Harbor for discharge,
Tung said.
</P>
<P>
"Our plans call for us to invest heavily in sewage system and
treatment works in other areas including the new towns and small
villages in New Territories, as well as protecting the Mai Po
Nature Reserve," he said. He added that such spending would
increase by 50 percent to 1.16 billion U.S. dollars in the next
five years.
</P>
<P>
The scheme is only part of the efforts Hong Kong will exert in
the coming few years to tackle the sewage problem and make Hong
Kong a clean, comfortable and pleasant home.
</P>
<P>
Tung gave top priority to environmental protection in his third
policy address with the theme of "quality people and quality home:
positioning Hong Kong for the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
"A real change in the quality of Hong Kong's environment needs
more than just cleaning up litter and enforcing environmental laws,
it requires a fundamental change of mindset," Tung noted.
</P>
<P>
The chief executive also announced a series of measures to
control air and water pollution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
