<HEADLINE> Organizers Confident of Having A Successful Gymnastics Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin is ready to host the
1999 Artistic Gymnastics World Championships slated for October 8-
16, an official of the organizing committee said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Everything is ready. We are ready to play host with our
enthusiasm and first-class service to the world championships,"
Sun Hailin, vice-president of the Organizing Committee, told a
press conference.
</P>
<P>
"We are glad all the preparation for the tournament goes well,
and no delegation complained about the gymnasium and apparatus so
far," said Sun, also vice-mayor of host city Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The organizers had feared that the preparation during the
intervals between two rotations could not be finished within the
limited 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
"Now we are confident that our staff can handle it without
problems in seven minutes through several rehearsals," said Gao
Jian, director of Competition Department.
</P>
<P>
The championships, the biggest and last meet of the kind in
this century, is the first ever organized in China since the
foundation of the International Gymnastics Federation (FIG) in
1881.
</P>
<P>
A total of 651 athletes from 72 countries and regions will
compete in the biennial event, which is also the last chance for
gymnasts to qualify for the 2000 Sydney Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Russian 1996 Olympic women's all-around champion Svetlana
Khorkina, and other big names including world champions Ivan
Ivankov of Belarus, Alexei Bondarenko of Russia and Simona Amanar
of Romania will also show up at this meet.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, spearheaded by world champions Li Xiaopeng,
Huang Xu and Lu Yufu, will defend the men's team title, while the
Chinese women gymnasts aim at making a breakthrough by winning
the title in the team competition. China took the women's team
silver medal in 1995, but finished third in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
