National Democratic Alliance will get a clear majority in the Lok
Sabha elections and that the results so far are in accordance with
its expectations.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether he was hopeful of becoming the prime minister
again, he merely smiled and said, "Let's see how the results
come."
</P>
<P>
Thanking the Delhi voters for electing all the seven BJP
candidates, he said the capital has created history once more.
</P>
<P>
"The victory is significant though Delhi has returned such a
verdict in the past too," he added.
</P>
<P>
In the 1998 elections, the BJP won only one seat out of seven
in Delhi, but it made a clean sweep Wednesday by winning seven
seats and re-establishing its stronghold in the country's capital.
 
