<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Says That Scientific Developments Need Commercial Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Vice-premier Li Lanqing said on
Wednesday that China's research and corporate worlds need to work
closely together for the commercial application of technological
developments.
</P>
<P>
Both the corporate world and the world of science and research
need to do so through various forms of cooperation, he said. Most
of the leading research institutes in China have no connection
with industry, and for this and other reasons, most of their
scientific and technological developments get shelved instead of
being put to commercial use.
</P>
<P>
As the information age approaches, he said, during a visit to
the Beijing Botanical Garden and a high-tech farming company, the
most important thing is knowledge, and, although a lot of
knowledge has been gained leading to a great number of
technological developments, only a small number of them have been
put to commercial use because of a missing link, which is the
commercial mechanism.
</P>
<P>
China needs to make an effort to establish that mechanism so
that technological developments can be put to commercial use as
soon as the market needs them. It is only by encouraging research
institutes to get taken over by industry or to be transformed into
enterprises that science and technology can play a greater role in
the economy and the economy can grow by leaps and bounds, he said.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has been using new technology in industry, agriculture,
communications, and environmental protection to promote economic
and social development and this is very promising and deserves
support, he concluded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
