<HEADLINE> Chinese President Part Of Audience For Russian Military Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Red Flag military
troupe performed a collection of Chinese and Russian folks songs
and dances here this evening for a Chinese audience that included
President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
The military troupe was established in 1928 and visited China
in 1952, 1965, and 1997. Chinese leaders like Mao Zedong, Zhou
Enlai, and Deng Xiaoping all expressed their appreciation for the
level of the performance, during those visits.
</P>
<P>
Prior to this evening's performance, Jiang spoke with some of
the actors and actresses taking part and said that this year is
the 50th anniversary of Sino-Russian diplomatic ties and that the
troupe's visit will enhance mutual understanding and friendship
between the Chinese and the Russians.
</P>
<P>
The audience grew quite excited when the troupe sang the
popular song "eulogizing the motherland" in Chinese, at the end of
the performance. And, after the show, Jiang got up on stage to
shake hands with the performers. 
</P>
