<HEADLINE> Philippines Passes Bill to Benefit Homeless </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine House of
Representatives has passed a bill increasing the capital stock of
the government-owned Home Insurance and Guarantee Corporation
(HIGC) to benefit the homeless, Philippine News Agency (PNA)
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the bill passed Tuesday night, the yearly capital
stock has been increased to 50 billion pesos (1.25 billion U.S.
dollars) from the previous 2.5 billion pesos (62.5 million
dollars), and the corporate life is also extended for another 50
years.
</P>
<P>
House Speaker Manuel Villar was quoted as saying the HIGC
guarantees loans made by home-buyers to private developers in mass
housing projects pushed by the government and this will surely
boost the government's mass housing drive and help provide shelter
to homeless Filipinos.
</P>
<P>
The bill, Villar said, will restore private-sector confidence
to resume investments and lending operations for the housing
industry and will also come up with affordable units for
low-income earners.
</P>
<P>
Villar said the proposed law likewise gives poor Filipinos
access to own homes. Mass housing and agriculture have been named
the two top priorities of the government in its poverty
eradication drive, he added.
</P>
<P>
With the Senate version of the bill already passed, Villar said
the bill would be passed into law soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
