<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Emphasizes Importance of Stability And Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Vice premier Wen Jiabao on
a fact-finding tour of north China's Hebei Province today
emphasized the importance of stability and agricultural
development, calling them the basis of sustainable and sound
economic development.
</P>
<P>
He said that maintaining stability and promoting agricultural
development are some of the major tasks in restructuring the
nation's economy and increasing domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
He said that there needs to be a restructuring of agriculture
and the rural economy and increased building of agricultural
infrastructure and increase of farmers' incomes. He asked local
officials and farmers to overcome the problems caused by natural
disasters and to lay a solid foundation for next year's harvests.
</P>
<P>
Wen visited Zhangbei and Huailai counties and talked with
people in hard-hit areas and had a look at the drought work there.
He said that a major task ahead in rural areas is more water
conservation projects and planting more trees and grass to improve
the environment.
</P>
<P>
He said that another task is focusing on higher-quality crops
and developing value-added farm produce and that there should be
measures to increase the incomes of farmers.
</P>
<P>
Parts of northern China have been hit by severe drought this
year. 
</P>
