<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK to Create Quality Living Environment: Tung </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 6 (Xinhua) - Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) said here
Wednesday that the SAR government would make efforts to create a
pleasant and safe living environment for the citizens.
</P>
<P>
Delivering his third policy address to the legislators, Tung
said that the government will take three measures for this
objective: first, implement urban renewal thoroughly; second,
protect the natural environment of the countryside; and third,
fully utilize and beautify the Victoria Harbor in an integrated
fashion.
</P>
<P>
The government intends to set up an Urban Renewal Authority (
URA) next year to replace the current Land Development Corporation
(LDC), which has been shouldering the arduous task of urban
renewal, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
The URA will be entrusted with powers to assemble land for
redevelopment to remove the obstacles of a protracted land
acquisition process and a shortage of rehousing resources the LDC
is facing.
</P>
<P>
"When the URA is established and the new initiatives are
implemented, we believe that all priority projects can be
completed within two decades, instead of three as previously
estimated," Tung told the 60-member Legislative Council.
</P>
<P>
The new approach to urban renewal aims at facilitating
comprehensive planning over larger areas, providing additional
open space, green belts, and community facilities and improving
road networks while preserving the distinctive features of the old
districts concerned.
</P>
<P>
"It is important to rehabilitate and preserve unique buildings
as this not only accords with our objective of sustainable
development but also facilitates the retention of the inherent
characteristics of different districts, and helps promote tourism,
" Tung said.
</P>
<P>
The government will review the existing heritage policy and
related legislation for better protection of historic buildings
and archaeological sites, he continued.
</P>
<P>
"Taking advantage of the beautiful natural landscape of Lantau
Island and Sai Kung District, we intend to develop these two areas
into centers of recreational and leisure activities compatible
with the principle of nature conservation," the chief executive
said.
</P>
<P>
To protect the Victoria Harbor, an integral part of Hong Kong
that all citizens treasure, the government has decided to scale
back the reclamation planned for the harbor.
</P>
<P>
"Moreover, we will make land available along the waterfront for
promenades and walkways so that our citizens and visitors can stay
away from the hubbub of the city, stroll along the promenades and
enjoy the beautiful scenery and refreshing sea breeze," he said.
</P>
<P>
"On the open space on both sides of the harbor from Lei Yue Mun
in the east to Kennedy Town in the west, we will provide open
plazas, landscaped areas, marinas, shops and restaurants with
distinct cultural flavors," he went on.
</P>
<P>
Traffic corridors along the waterfront should be built as
underground or semi-submerged roads to alleviate noise and air
pollution as well as to improve the visual aspect, Tung said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
