<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive Confident of Economic Recovery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 6 (Xinhua) - Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) said here
Wednesday that he is confident that Hong Kong's economy will
continue to pick up as the most difficult times have passed.
</P>
<P>
Delivering his Policy Address to the Legislative Council
Wednesday afternoon, Tung said that Hong Kong's economy is showing
signs of turning the corner as the various relief measures taken
by the government in the past two years steadily produce results
and the Asian financial turmoil slowly subsides.
</P>
<P>
Recently, there has been a gradual revival of consumer
sentiment and Hong Kong's export trade has picked up, Tung said.
The number of inbound tourists has been on the rise and the stock
and property markets have stabilized, he added.
</P>
