<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Succeeds Politically, Economically in Past Two Years: Tung </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa
said here Wednesday that the Hong Kong government has been
successful in implementing the "one country, two systems" concept
in Hong Kong and in riding out the Asian financial storm in the
past two years.
</P>
<P>
Delivering his Policy Address at the Legislative Council here
Wednesday afternoon, Tung said that over the past two years, Hong
Kong has experienced two momentous changes -- Hong Kong's
reunification with the motherland and the considerable
readjustment to the economy triggered by the regional and even
global effects of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
On July 1, 1997, the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (
SAR) government came into being under the principle of "Hong Kong
people running Hong Kong".
</P>
<P>
"On the same day, we established the Court of Final Appeal in
the spirit of true judicial independence," Tung said. "We also
formed the Provisional Legislative Council and subsequently held
elections for the first Legislative Council of the SAR," he said.
</P>
<P>
All these fundamental changes have taken place smoothly, and,
at the same time, there has been no change in Hong Kong's economic
and legal systems, Tung added. "People's way of life has remained
much the same. Freedoms, including that of speech and of assembly,
have been safeguarded," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong remains a separate customs territory that cooperates
directly with the international community in areas such as
protecting intellectual property rights and fighting against drugs
and smuggling. "We also exercise our own stringent control on the
import and export of strategic commodities," he said.
</P>
<P>
The trend of mass emigration in the run-up to the handover has
now reversed to a flow of returnees.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, last year, even at the height of the regional
financial turmoil, there were over 23,000 transactions in new
private residential properties and over 33,000 in subsidized flats
under the Home Ownership Scheme, Tenants Purchase Scheme, Flat-for-
Sale Scheme and Sandwich Class Housing Scheme.
</P>
<P>
In total, people committed over 100 billion HK dollars to buy
their own homes here in Hong Kong. Even in the face of economic
volatility, these families have cast their vote of confidence in
Hong Kong's future with their assets and actions, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is subjected to severe blows of the financial crisis,
Tung said. "Our financial system came under immense pressure in
the summer of 1998. We faced speculative attacks in local stock
and foreign exchange markets. Confidence in our financial system
was shaken," he continued.
</P>
<P>
Under the circumstances, the SAR government, through the Hong
Kong Monetary Authority, made the decisive and timely decision to
enter the markets and stabilized them, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
"The decision was widely criticized at that time. In retrospect,
exceptional though it was, we made the correct move," Tung
stressed.
</P>
<P>
"We have since adopted a series of measures to strengthen the
linked exchange rate regime and our financial system's defense,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
"This has consolidated Hong Kong's position as an
international financial center and the sudden arrival of the
financial turmoil only speeded up the necessary readjustment of
our economy," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
