with his Portuguese counterpart Antonio Guterres. During the talks
with Portuguese Prime Minister Antonio Guterres, the two
government leaders discussed top issues on the agenda for the
upcoming mid-October EU summit in the Finnish city of Tempere, and
a special meeting of the EU leadership. (Portugal-EU-Judicial
Cooperation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. House of Representatives Tuesday
approved a foreign aid bill that will reduce the country's foreign
aid funding.
</P>
<P>
President Bill Clinton, who last week promised to relieve one
billion U.S. dollars in debt owed by the poorest countries, has
indicated that his administration will veto the bill. The bill
offers "woefully inadequate" funding for foreign aid, Clinton said
in a letter to House Speaker Dennis Hastert on September 30.
Democrats in the House complain that the bill does not match the "
leadership role" of the United States in the world, while
Republicans say there isn't any more money for foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
An earlier version of the legislation, which was compromised by
the House and Senate negotiators, was approved by a vote of 214-
211 on a partisan line. (US-House-Aid Bill)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
