Kachornprasart was quoted as saying on Wednesday that the police
were instructed to increase their presence outside all the
diplomatic missions; while inside, the foreign embassies were
responsible for arranging and managing their own security measures.
Security procedures at Maneeloy Holding Center for Myanmese
refugees in the province of Rachaburi would also be reviewed, as
two of the five armed Myanmese students, who held 96 people as
hostages, came from the center, he said. (Thailand-Foreign
Embassies-Security)
