<HEADLINE> South Asia Should Join Hands for Energy Resource: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Foreign Minister Dr.
Ram Sharan Mahat said that South Asian countries should speed up
their efforts to make optimal use of their energy resource
endowments to better develop their economies, the official RSS
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a conference on regional cooperation in South Asia
organized by Foreign and Common Wealth Office of the United
Kingdom in London, Mahat said Nepal's vast water resources could
be used not only for generating electricity which could earn
revenue for Nepal, but could also bring external benefits such as
irrigation, flood control and navigation for the lower riparian
countries.
</P>
