Bangladesh, they could be brought in to share the investment cost
also within the framework of regional cooperation, Mahat said.
</P>
<P>
Mahat also said that to bring down the investment cost of
hydropower and produce electricity at an affordable price, South
Asian countries should make their economies more business-friendly
and attractive to international investors, adding that policy
shifts under unstable political situations raise risks and push up
the cost.
</P>
<P>
The conference with its theme "South Asia: How Can Closer
Regional Cooperation be Achieved?" is taken place in London on
October 4-8, said RSS. 
