<HEADLINE> SOCOG: One Third of Sydney Olympics Tickets Order Fully Filled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- One third of people who applied
for tickets to next year's Olympics have had their order
completely filled, Sydney organisers said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Sixty percent of people will get more than half of what they
ordered, and one in three people will have their order completely
filled," said John Bosiljevac, ticket operations manager of the
Sydney Organising Committee of the Olympic Games (SOCOG).
</P>
<P>
"There will inevitably be some disappointment," he said. "In
our case, we treated everyone equally by running a ballot."
</P>
<P>
Bosiljevac said a quarter of applications were unable to be
matched in the ballot, but said in many cases, people only missed
out altogether on high demand tickets, such as the D category
cheapest tickets for the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Applicants who have ordered tickets will begin receiving their
confirmation packages Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Those who didn't get everything they wanted will have two weeks
to apply for other tickets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
