<HEADLINE> Singapore, Latvia Sign Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Singapore and Latvia signed
Wednesday two agreements on air services to facilitate the
development of trade, investment and tourism and further
strengthen bilateral relations, the Singapore Communications
Ministry said in a statement Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Air Services Agreement (ASA) and the Agreement for the
Avoidance of Double Taxation and the Prevention of Fiscal Evasion
with respect to Taxes on Income were signed by representatives
from Latvia's Transport Ministry and the Singapore Communications
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The ASA provides a framework for the respective flag carriers
to establish air links between the two countries, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
The other agreement on the two countries' taxation arrangements
is the 43rd comprehensive tax treaty which Singapore has signed,
according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
The second agreement will serve to prevent double taxation of
income earned in one country by a resident of the other, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
It will also make clear the taxing rights between Singapore and
Latvia on all forms of income which arise as a consequence of
cross-border economic activities between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
It also provides for reduction or exemption of tax at source on
certain types of income, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Currently, 63 airlines link Singapore to 151 cities with over
3,100 weekly scheduled flights. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
