contracts to repair Russia's palaces and government buildings.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The European Commission has asked France to justify by
Friday its refusal to lift embargo on British beef products, while
London has called for a boycott of French farm products. France,
backed by Germany, has asked EU to call a meeting of its
commission of experts on the situation of ``mad cow'' disease in
Britain, because Brussels did not do so when deciding to lifting
embargo on British beefs two months ago.
</P>
<P>
-- Between 1991 and 1997, the wealth of French people increased
by 12 percent, mainly due to investigation in stock markets and
financial ventures. But the increase of the wealth of French
nation, which now stands at 26,000 billion francs (4,333 billion U.
S. dollars), has resulted in a widening of the gap of ownership
between the rich and the poor, with 10 percent of Frenchmen and
Frenchwomen owning 65 percent of the national wealth. 
