<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Host Animal Protection Workshop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The South African Society
for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals (SPCA) is to host the
first Pan-African animal protection workshop in Johannesburg
between October 12 and 16.
</P>
<P>
SPCA Executive Director Marcel French said in a statement on
Wednesday that the workshop would be presented by the Humane
Society of the United States.
</P>
<P>
More than 60 delegates from Zimbabwe, Uganda and Namibia, and
the International Fund for Animal Welfare are expected to attend.
</P>
<P>
French said the delegates were to share valuable information,
experience in animal protection, and a great deal of professional
expertise.
</P>
<P>
The workshop will center on such topics as animal trade and
welfare in South Africa, exotic animals in shelters, wildlife in
circuses, humane treatment and the handling of livestock,
sterilization methods and investigating cruelty. 
</P>
