<HEADLINE> 3 Kenyan Children Killed In Grenade Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Three children were killed and
four other people seriously injured Tuesday when a hand grenade
exploded in a village of Kenya's Coast Province, East African
Standard reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the grenade was one of those planted during
the struggle for Kenya's independence from the British colonial
rule in the 1960s.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred when the children, who had played one
foot from their house, hit an object, which was protruding above
the ground and exploded instantly.
</P>
<P>
A team of bomb experts had been dispatched to the spot to
initiate investigations.
</P>
<P>
The police in the area appealed to the residents to avoid any
suspicious objects and report such cases to them.
</P>
<P>
Last month, two children were killed in Central Province's
capital Nyeri when a landmine which was planted over 30 years ago
blew up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
