<HEADLINE> 5-Seater Plane Crashes in Central Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- A 5-seater light plane crashed at
about 10 a.m. Wednesday in the mountains of the central Philippine
province of Catanduanes, reports reaching here said Wednesday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Office of Civil Defense (OCD) in the city of San Andres,
Catanduanes, said the airplane was ferrying foreign investors
visiting the island province, Philippine News Agency (PNA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
But so far no reports are available on how many people there
are on board. Actually the provincial authority even could not
confirm where the foreign investors may come from.
</P>
<P>
The PNA quoted Jose Mapa, provincial administrator, as saying
that they often have visitors who come by helicopter but he was
not informed beforehand. He added that they usually send notice
before coming over.
</P>
<P>
Police and Red Cross rescuers, backed up by mountaineers have
set on foot towards the mountains in San Andres hoping to confirm
or find a trace of the wreckage, the PNA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
