<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Fisheries Output Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's fisheries industry has
reported output of 1.38 million tons in the first nine months of
the year, a 13.82 percent increase on the year-earlier period,
Vietnam's business newspaper The Saigon Times Daily reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A report on Vietnam's fisheries says that fishing is now very
favorable as the southern fishing grounds have entered the peak
season. September output of the sector is posted at 107,000 tons,
4 percent above the average of the first eight months.
</P>
<P>
Seafood output reached 931,870 tons in the first nine months
while aqua-product farms obtained output of 447,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
In the period the country's aqua-product exports grew 12.74
percent in value over the same period of last year to 690 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
September export receipts, however, fell to 85 million U.S.
dollars from the more than 100 million U.S. dollars in the
previous month.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the year's aqua-product export sales target of 950
million U.S. dollars, Vietnam's Ministry of Fisheries has urged
major coastal cities and provinces to take measures to control
natural disaster, raise a second shrimp crop in favorable areas
and import materials for export processing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
