<HEADLINE> Macao Police Seize Raw Materials for CD Piracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Macao police on Tuesday seized a
large amount of smuggled raw materials for the production of
compact discs, the Macao Daily New reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Acting on some secret information, Macao police intercepted a
truck Tuesday afternoon at the Barrier Gate. The truck was
reported to be loaded with gumwater.
</P>
<P>
However, about 40 percent of the 698 cans were found to contain
colloidal granules which can be used to produce 190,000 pieces of
compact discs.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the truck was taken to the police station for
further investigation.
</P>
<P>
Local police sources said that smugglers have been racking
their brains to transport pirated CDs or raw materials for CD
production. And the cans detected this time were just mingled with
other cargo and stacked in the lower layers in the truck.
</P>
<P>
Police said that they will take more actions in an effort to
eradicate CD piracy in Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
