<DOCNO> XIE19991006.0228 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Guinean Ties Hailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) held a reception
here today to mark the 40th anniversary of the establishment of
diplomatic relations between China and Guinea.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen and his wife Zhou Hanqiong,
together with other senior Chinese officials, attended the
reception.
</P>
<P>
CPAFFC President Qi Huaiyuan said on the occasion that
bilateral ties have been developing steadily since the forging of
diplomatic ties four decades ago despite the changing
international situation, adding that there have been constant high-
level exchanges of visits, and mutual understanding between the
two sides has been promoted.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries have always supported each other
in the international arena. Qi also expressed his appreciation and
thanks for the Guinean government's adherence to the one China
policy and its support in the United Nations conference on human
rights.
</P>
<P>
He noted that bilateral ties have been established based on
equality, sincerity, friendship, unity, cooperation and common
development, saying that the two countries have had fruitful
cooperation in the economy, trade, health, culture and technology
in various forms.
</P>
<P>
There exist broad prospects and big potential for bilateral
cooperation, Qi said, and added he believes that with joint
efforts of both governments and peoples, Sino-Guinean friendship
and cooperation will continue to grow in the years ahead.
</P>
<P>
Guinea's ambassador to China Mamady Conde said that Guinea, as
the first country south of Sahara to recognize China, will
continue to pursue the one China policy and support China on the
human rights issue.
</P>
<P>
Guinea will never barter away its principles, and will stand by
China, he said.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said that Guinean President Lansana Conte
visited China twice, thus consolidating Sino-Guinean friendship,
adding that bilateral ties have entered a period of maturity,
which will benefit both sides.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his thanks for China's economic assistance to
Guinea over the past years.
</P>
<P>
Those present on the occasion included President Conte's wife
Hacja Kadiatou Seth Conte and Guinean Minister of Agriculture and
Livestock Jean Paul Sarr. 
</P>
</TEXT>
