<HEADLINE> Sichuan Week At China's Kunming Horticulture Exposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- China's Sichuan Province had a
special celebration week here today as part of the '99 World
Horticulture Exposition.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan is on the middle reaches of the Yangtze River and the
home of pandas, Xu Shiqun, its vice-governor, said at the opening
ceremony. Sichuan wants to show its efforts in environmental
protection and its beautiful scenery at the exposition, he added.
</P>
<P>
At a news conference here Tuesday, 9 national-level scenic
spots, 11 national forest parks, and 7 historical cities in the
province were described at an indoor photo display, multimedia
show, and a TV wall. The province has built a Shufeng Garden
outside showing Sichuan's tourism resources and gardening art,
with historical notes, poems, books, paintings, and landscapes.
</P>
<P>
The celebration will also have theatrical performances and
business activities. 
</P>
