<HEADLINE> Six Zambians Arrested for Growing Cannabis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Drug Enforcement
Commission (DEC) has arrested six farmers in connection with
illegal cultivation of cannabis.
</P>
<P>
DEC spokesperson Mukutulu Sinyani who confirmed the arrest
Tuesday said the suspects were found to have cultivated 180
kilogram of cannabis in the Chirundu area, Southern Province.
</P>
<P>
Zambia's Daily Mail Wednesday quoted Sinyani as saying DEC made
the arrest during their continuous operations in an effort to
probe illegal drug dealers.
</P>
<P>
He said the six were charged with cultivation and being in
possession of narcotic drugs and would soon appear before court.
</P>
