<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Hits Bazaar in Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- A fire hit one of the biggest
bazaars in the northern Philippine city of Baguio early Wednesday
morning even as the city suffered from continuous downpour and
gusty winds caused by typhoon, Philippine News Agency (PNA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
The PNA quoted Virgilio Hidalgo, spokesman of the local police,
as saying that the fire starting to rage in a five-story
commercial building at 5:00 a.m. has already destroyed thousand
pesos worth of properties despite absence of any casualty.
</P>
<P>
Hidalgo added that firemen from the city and surrounding
communities are still battling the raging fire in the building but
find it hard to contain the fire due to lack of equipment like gas
masks and unavailability of a fire hydrant.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, landslides triggered by typhoon "Pepang" resulted in
the closure of many roads in the region.
</P>
<P>
City social welfare officer Betty Fangasan said her office is
also trying to determine possible evacuation sites for flooded
families.
</P>
<P>
Aside from flooded houses, the City Disaster Coordinating
Council is also convincing other occupants of landslide prone
areas to evacuate their houses before darkness sets in. 
</P>
</TEXT>
