<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's 10th National Book Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Changsha, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Monday was the last day of the
10th National Book Fair in China, in Changsha, the capital of
Hunan Province, which opened on September 24.
</P>
<P>
The Hunan delegation ranked No.1 of all delegations in amount
of business. There were some 24 delegations present, as well as
500 publishing houses and 400 periodicals represented, making it
the largest fair of its kind.
</P>
<P>
A set of law books published by the People's Publishing House
and a set of books explaining how to make a fortune from the
Jiangsu Technology Publishing House were among the top sellers,
according to the fair's business office.
</P>
<P>
The fair had more than 140,000 titles available and over 1,600,
000 visitors, 730,000 of them from rural areas.
</P>
<P>
China's first National Book Fair opened in Beijing in 1980.
Over the years it has turned into a festival not only for
publishers but for many readers from across the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
