<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Implement Recovery Budget in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will implement a
recovery budget next year to get the economy back on a firm
footing, Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"I can assure you that everything will be done in order to get
the economy back on a firm footing so that everybody will enjoy
prosperity in this country," he said at a press conference upon
his returning from a two-week working visit to New York, London
and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
The budget for 2000 is scheduled to be presented in Parliament
on October 29.
</P>
<P>
On Malaysia's economic growth, Mahathir said the National
Economic Action Council's executive committee has been looking at
the third quarter figures on a month by month basis. "And the
figures look good," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said the one percent growth (rate) set by the government for
this year can be achieved.
</P>
<P>
Some economists have predicted that Malaysia's economic growth
could even exceed 5.0 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
For the first half of this year, Malaysia's economy recorded a
growth of 1.4 percent against a contraction of 7.5 percent last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
