<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, October 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- Renewed wrangling over wines and spirits is
threatening to unravel the long-awaited trade, development and
cooperation deal between the European Union and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Four years in the making, the deal is due to be signed soon in
Pretoria. Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari, who is also the EU
president, is scheduled to attend the signing ceremony, government
sources said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Officials from both sides were feverishly working to overcome
differences on the fine print of crucial areas of the draft
agreement. They center on the wines and spirits agreement which
forms part of the overall pact. (SAfrica-EU-Trade)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Thailand's economic recovery is now underway and
the 1999 growth is expected to reach 3-4 percent, the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) announced on Tuesday. IMF's
executive board approved Tuesday the completion of the eighth
review under Thailand's Stand-By Arrangement, allowing the Thai
authorities to draw a further 500 million U.S. dollars from the
financial bailout package. (IMF-Thailand)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- The inflation reached 7.76 percent in
Colombia in the first nine months of 1999, the lowest in the past
29 years, the National Department of Statistics said on Tuesday.
(Colombia-Inflation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LUSAKA -- The Regional Tourism Organization of Southern Africa
(RETOSA) has embarked on a global marketing strategy to increase
the flow of tourists to the Southern African Development Community
(SADC) region.
</P>
<P>
RETOSA Executive Director Shepherd Nyaruwata said the strategy
had been designed to prop up the image of southern Africa as the
ultimate tourist destination. (SADC-Tourism)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
YANGON-- The value of the bilateral trade between Myanmar and
Singapore amounted to 256.66 million U.S. dollars in the first
four months of this year, an increase of 2.75 percent over the
same period of last year when it stood at 249.77 million dollars.
(Myanmar-Trade)  
</P>
