<HEADLINE> Death Toll Rises to 50 in Bus Accident in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The death toll in bus accident
in West Java, Indonesia, had risen to 50 on Tuesday, national
newspapers reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred on Monday midnight in Cianjur, about 100
kilometers south of Jakarta, when a bus plying the Jakarta-Bandung
route struck a cliff wall.
</P>
<P>
At total of 45 passengers died on the spot, and other five died
in hospital.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the 28 passengers, who were severely injured were
being treated at the intensive care units of Pacet and Sayang
hospitals, both in Cianjur.
</P>
<P>
Cianjur Police chief Lt. Col. Fadjar Purnomo said police were
undertaking a preliminary investigation, but were already able to
cite two likely causes.
</P>
<P>
"our provisional suspicion is that the driver was driving
recklessly or the brakes were damaged," Fadjar was quoted by the
Jakarta Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
He also said this was the worst road accident during the last
two years in his region.
</P>
<P>
One of the injured survivors Dodo said the bus was traveling
quickly, but steadily on its way until it reached a corner in the
Lembah Hijau area in Puncak.
</P>
<P>
He said as the bus rounded the corner, it swayed to the left
and hit the cliff wall.
</P>
<P>
The bus had a capacity load, and was perhaps overcrowded, with
78 passengers.
</P>
<P>
The hilly area of Puncak, filled with tea plantations, becomes
crowded and its traffic jams during weekends as many Jakarta
inhabitants spend their weekends out of town to relax. 
</P>
</TEXT>
