<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guinean Ambassador on Sino-Guinean Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This year marks the 40th anniversary of the establishment of
diplomatic relations between the Republic of Guinea and the People
's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Chairman Mao Zedong and President Ahmed Sekou Toure attached
great importance to the bilateral relations. The two sides
cooperated in wide-ranging fields, such as agriculture,
stockbreeding, fishery, education and training, industry and
infrastructure, said the Ambassador.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the relationship between the two nations is based
on real friendship between the two peoples, mutual-respect, non-
interference in each other's internal affairs, mutual-support in
international affairs and effective mutual-cooperation, adding
that Guinea has always adhered to the "One China" policy, and that
China has offered unselfish assistance to Guinea's social and
economic development.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of China's reform and opening up drive, he commented
that China has made impressive achievements over the past 20 years,
and that the Chinese people and government will continue the grand
reform and opening up cause.
</P>
<P>
The Ambassador is very optimistic about future Sino-Guinean
relations, saying that the prospect of the relations is bright.
</P>
<P>
He said that the bilateral cooperation has experienced new
progress in recent years after Guinean President Lansana Conte's
visit to China in 1996, and that the two sides are expecting new
results of cooperation in aviation and exploration of Guinea's
mineral resources.
</P>
<P>
The Guinean people, government and President Lansana Conte
cherish sincere friendship with China, and wish an early
realization of China's reunification, said the Ambassador, adding
that the Guinean government will never change its "One China"
policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
