<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's University Sets up News Media Lab </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- A news media laboratory was
recently set up in the People's University under the help of
Beijing University's Founder Group Corp., one of China's major
manufacturers of computer hardware and software.
</P>
<P>
According to today's China Youth Daily, the new lab with
advanced technologies in press, publication, radio, television,
internet and advertisement will be used to train professional
journalists and editors.
</P>
<P>
The Founder Group gave assistance to establish a simulative
medium-sized newspaper office in the lab. Students may study and
experience the whole process of report from news gathering, ads
and pictures management to newspaper publication with new
technologies in the lab. 
</P>
