<HEADLINE> France Provides 2.9 Million for Cambodian Electric Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, October 6 (Xinhua) -- French government Tuesday
granted 2.9 million U.S. dollars to Electricite du Cambodge for
improving its business and management.
</P>
<P>
French Ambassador Andre-Jean Libourel and Minister of Industry
Suy Sem signed the grant agreement.
</P>
<P>
Electricite du Cambodge will soon start working on improving
its customer services, billing system and other business
operations to benefit 100,000 customers in Phnom Penh, according
to Wednesday's Cambodia Daily.
</P>
<P>
