<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, October 5 (Xinhua) -- American states will sign a "
Mechanism for the Multilateral Evaluation Agreement (MEM)" on
October 7, at the end of the 26th session of the Inter-American
Commission for the control of drug abuse.
</P>
<P>
The MEM will permit the establishment of a common rule for
evaluating the efforts, both by an individual state and throughout
the hemisphere, in fighting against drugs.
</P>
<P>
The mechanism will be transformed into an instrument for
international cooperation within the framework of the hemispheric
anti-drug strategy.
</P>
