<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stock End Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stock ended mixed
Tuesday in a cautious response to the Federal Reserve's decision
to leave the interest rates unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 0.64 at 10,400.59,
erasing all the 105-point gain in the trading.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly lower. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index fell 3.25 at 1,301.35 but the technology heavy
Nasdaq composite index rose 3.70 at 2,799.67.
</P>
<P>
The Dow index turned negative after the Federal Reserve
announced that it decided not to raise interest rates but moved
its policy directive from neutral to one tilting toward a rate
increase in the coming months. The blue chip index surged in the
early trading as investors expected the Federal Reserve to leave
the rates alone.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said investors made a nervous response to the Federal
Reserve's announcement because the decision did not clear the air
of uncertainty on the rate future.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index fell 1.29 at 599.30 and the American Stock
Exchange index fell 5.18 at 784.65. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies fell 0.60 at 426.01.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a nearly 3-to-2
margin on the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,794 down, 1,241 up
and 505 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 954.23 million shares from 795.96
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
